libtestgear
------------------------------------------
This is the Test Gear client library which offers an API for communicating with
Test Gear device servers. The API allows client applications to
connect/disconnect, load/unload plugins, query/manage variables (parameters),
and run commands (functions).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libtestgear-devel-0.2+git20141022-1bl1
  libtestgear0-0.2+git20141022-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/testgear/libtestgear

Canonical download:
  git://github.com/testgear/libtestgear.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libtestgear-0.2+git20141022-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libtestgear-0.2+git20141022-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libtestgear-0.2+git20141022-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtestgear-0.2+git20141022-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtestgear0-0.2+git20141022-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtestgear-devel-0.2+git20141022-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libtestgear)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libtestgear.README
  /usr/share/doc/libtestgear/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libtestgear/README

(libtestgear0)
  /usr/bin/cygtestgear-0.dll

(libtestgear-devel)
  /usr/include/testgear/testgear.h
  /usr/lib/libtestgear.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libtestgear.pc

